  "prompt": "What is Tacometer?",
  "response": "A tachometer is an instrument that measures the rotational speed of an object, typically a shaft or disk, in a machine or engine. It is commonly used in vehicles to measure the engine's revolutions per minute (RPM). Tachometers help in monitoring and optimizing the performance of engines and other machinery by providing real-time data on their operational speed. They can be analog, with a needle and dial, or digital, with an electronic display. In automotive applications, tachometers are crucial for keeping engines running at optimal speeds and preventing damage from over-revving.",
